{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Comprehensive live reconciler validation + guaranteed bilateral cleanup\n\n## Why\nProve the reconciler's correctness end-to-end against live Jira. An agent with ACLI access runs the full\nbidirectional matrix and GUARANTEES cleanup of every test artifact in both systems. NOTE: this validates the\nPOST-FIX behavior, so it runs AFTER the C-band fixes land (C1/C2/C3/C4) — several signals below are the TARGET\nbehavior those tickets create (e.g. C3 today only prints to stderr; C3 adds the BRIDGE_ALERT asserted here).\nOrdering captured here rather than as hard `depends_on` edges to avoid blocking-link hierarchy promotion across\nmixed-type siblings; the harness build may start early, the matrix run gates on the C-band.\n\n## Signal definitions (each an observable pass criterion)\n- C1 (conflict signal): the conflict record C1 (feline-wandering-dassierat) defines is emitted on a both-sides\n  mirrored-field divergence (assert against the exact key/field C1 lands — reference C1, do not hard-code an\n  unverified `reason=\"conflict\"`).\n- C2 (hard-delete -> re-create): after a Jira hard-delete, a NEW issue with the SAME `rebar-id:<local_id>` label +\n  entity property is created and bound; NO false \"re-created\" comment (lowerclass-creased-fruitbat).\n- C3 (field-allowlist-drop alert): the deduped BRIDGE_ALERT that C3 (nonglacial-tense-vulture) adds fires when an\n  outbound field is dropped (today the code only prints to stderr — assert the post-C3 alert).\n- C4 (429/Retry-After): monkey-patch the path C4 implements (per lambswool-shaded-eider). Default target: the\n  REST-style `acli_subprocess._call_with_backoff` (reads headers ~line 267) — return 429 + `Retry-After: 2` on the\n  first call and assert a >=2 s backoff then success. If C4 lands only on the plain subprocess path, patch that.\n- Echo suppression: outbound comments carry `<!-- rebar:reconciler-echo -->`; field/status writes are baseline-seeded\n  via ProvenanceLedger (differ.py) so they are not re-ingested — verify by `mutation_count==0` on the next pass over\n  the just-written data (harness pre-seeds the baseline exactly as a real pass would).\n- Status round-trip incl. LOSSY labels: set local `blocked` (a lossy status with no faithful live Jira state) ->\n  assert Jira shows the nearest live status + a `rebar-status:blocked` annotation label -> next inbound pass restores\n  local `blocked`; and `idea<->IDEA` round-trips with no annotation. No oscillation over N passes.\n- TOMBSTONE/GRACE: local archive -> Jira Done (not deleted); a Jira 404 observed on N consecutive passes\n  (N = `RECONCILER_ABSENT_RETIRE_GRACE`, default 3) -> the binding is soft-retired to `bindings-retired.json`; a\n  single 404 does NOT retire.\n- Blast-radius breaker: with >=11 synthetic bindings, one acting decision (fraction 0.09) does NOT trip; a synthetic\n  mass-change (> the 0.10 fraction) trips it — asserted via the `refused` census/verdict the breaker emits (not a bare \"trips\").\n\n## Harness (guaranteed bilateral teardown)\n- pytest autouse fixture `yield`+`finally` (or bash `trap cleanup EXIT`) that hard-deletes Jira test issues AND\n  discards the local throwaway env — runs even on assertion failure/exception.\n- Teardown-failure fallback: each cleanup call retries-with-backoff (3x); on exhaustion append the id to\n  `leaked-artifacts.log` and exit non-zero (loud, never silent).\n- Setup probe: create one throwaway issue and assert `client.delete_issue` returns `{\"status\":\"deleted\"}` (NOT a 403\n  soft-fail — `acli.py:716-720` swallows PermissionError) so teardown can actually delete.\n\n## Isolation, credentials\n- Dedicated Jira TEST project; a service account with \"Delete Issues\" scoped to that project only (project role, not\n  global); token injected via a secret, never logged/committed.\n- Local side: an ISOLATED throwaway tickets env/branch (worktree) discarded post-run (append-only events must not\n  pollute production history). Do NOT rely on local delete.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Harness with GUARANTEED bilateral teardown; a teardown-under-failure test injects a RuntimeError after create and asserts BOTH artifacts are cleaned.\n- [ ] One observable pass criterion PER matrix scenario above (C1-C4, echo, status-round-trip incl. lossy labels, tombstone/grace, idempotency mutation_count==0, blast-radius trip) — each with the signal defined above; harness exits 0 all-green and attaches a JSON/JUnit report.\n- [ ] Teardown-failure fallback (retry+`leaked-artifacts.log`+non-zero exit); ZERO surviving artifacts on success.\n- [ ] Delete-permission probe passes; credential scoped to the test project + injected via secret.\n- [ ] Isolation documented (test project + throwaway local env); production REB + tickets branch untouched.\n- [ ] Runs after the C-band fixes land; re-runnable (idempotent teardown). Harness pattern recorded in an ADR/design note.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783476730326825001,"uuid":"a0e3f41c-c2ae-4ccc-885e-20dd649aa91b"}